The paper discusses the use of LiDAR sensors for autonomous driving, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The processing and learning of 3D point clouds is a key aspect of this technology, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques for autonomous driving, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV and cs.RO, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CL.
